## Strategic Interpretation

The strongest next push is not only BuildLang/buildc, and not only Telos
accountability. It is the layer that connects them: a scientific runtime
receipt that can bind source intake, formal target, exact oracle, executable
runtime branch, compiler/runtime state, numerical drift, negative fixture,
Crucible verdict, and action receipt.

That gives the system a plausible cross-field shape:

- math and theorem proving use formal target packets and countermodels;
- quantum and physics use claim-boundary packets and measurement receipts;
- theoretical CS uses counterexample revision workbenches;
- agent research uses looped verifier/action receipts;
- BuildLang/buildc becomes the accountable runtime layer where compiled
  scientific kernels can be measured, replayed, and compared against exact
  or reference oracles;
- color calibration and rendering become the visual-truth version of the same
  receipt model.

Every bullet above remains a product hypothesis until backed by executable
receipts and Crucible verdicts.

